&lt;p&gt;So, this question is essentially a request to share (post and/or link to) your configuration - or maybe even configurations of others you found useful. So that beginners have a starting point and experienced users a source of inspiration. There may be a lot of &lt;em&gt;i3&lt;/em&gt; configurations available around the Internet, but this site is the only one that is actually linked from the offical &lt;em&gt;i3&lt;/em&gt; website.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5144/where-can-i-find-examples-for-i3-configurations/?answer=5150#post-id-5150</link><description>Not sure this is a good place to dump blobs of personal preferences. Next to questions of readability, I have had bad experiences with copy pasting a configuration that did not grow over time.  My fingers do not have photographic(?) memory, and the configuration of an interactive tool should be minimal and slowly develop and grow with you. 

That being said, I believe [dotshare.it](http://dotshare.it) has some sound ideas about presenting and sharing config files. They host an interesting [collection of `i3`-configs](http://dotshare.it/category/wms/i3/). </description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2014 00:39:27 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5144/where-can-i-find-examples-for-i3-configurations/?answer=5150#post-id-5150</guid></item><item><title>Comment by daedalus.mythos for &lt;p&gt;Not sure this is a good place to dump blobs of personal preferences. Next to questions of readability, I have had bad experiences with copy pasting a configuration that did not grow over time.  My fingers do not have photographic(?) memory, and the configuration of an interactive tool should be minimal and slowly develop and grow with you. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That being said, I believe &lt;a href="http://dotshare.it"&gt;dotshare.it&lt;/a&gt; has some sound ideas about presenting and sharing config files. They host an interesting &lt;a href="http://dotshare.it/category/wms/i3/"&gt;collection of &lt;code&gt;i3&lt;/code&gt;-configs&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
